-- Romania’s Patriciu in Talks to Sell Mic.ro to 7-Eleven, ZF Says
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-01-20T07:51:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/romania-s-patriciu-in-talks-to-sell-mic-ro-to-7-eleven-zf-says.html
Romanian businessman Dinu Patriciu
is in talks with Seven & I Holdings Co., which owns the 7-Eleven
convenience-store franchise, to sell his Mic.ro chain, Ziarul
Financiar  reported  today, citing unidentified people in the
retail business.  The talks began last autumn and may to be completed in
March; Patriciu seeks to sell Mic.ro, which has overdue debts,
to suppliers and banks, the Bucharest-based newspaper said.  The talks are focused on possible provision of 60 million
euros ($78 million) of fresh capital for the chain, which
Patriciu owns through a company called Mercadia Holland, ZF
said, adding that Mercadia Holland officials wouldn’t comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
